    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a definitive example of the high-revving S54 platform. This chassis features a meticulously maintained 3.2L inline-six, delivering 333hp through six individual throttle bodies with a crisp 8,000 RPM redline. The double-VANOS system has been fully overhauled with upgraded seals, and the rear subframe\u2014a known structural fatigue point\u2014has been proactively reinforced to ensure torsional rigidity under heavy lateral G-loads. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox provides tactile engagement, free of synchro wear, while the variable M differential lock ensures optimal torque distribution. The exterior retains its factory-depth paint with no orange peel or rock chips, and the undercarriage is free of oxidation. This vehicle represents a zero-compromise mechanical specimen for the purist collector.",
